race.comment: A good race. BAZABALL REWARDED (8) won comfortably here first up and then returned and demolished the 62 graders by 5L from the speed, backed off the map. She has been freshened and has plenty of scope for improvement. Uses the low barrier and the hat-trick beckons. DELICATE LADY (7) brought strong form to Bendigo and didn't do a bad job after settling last from a wide barrier. The gate is a little better today and she has some weight relief. She's up to winning if things go her way. DREAMS (9) resumes and two back led and blitzed the Moonee Valley Maidens by 6L. Brown sticks from that in a key jockey engagement, and she has two jumpouts under the saddle with the in-form rider aboard. Everything points to a bold return. UNSNOOZUAL (6) will be around the mark building on the expected Maiden win at Echuca.
